1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,410
Here is how you can develop your power to see what can be, not just what is.

2
00:00:05,679 --> 00:00:09,890
I call these the practice adding value exercises.

3
00:00:09,890 --> 00:00:11,090
1.

4
00:00:11,280 --> 00:00:13,729
Practice adding value to things.

5
00:00:13,920 --> 00:00:16,050
Remember the real estate example.

6
00:00:16,240 --> 00:00:22,449
Ask yourself, what can I do to add value to this room or this house or this business?

7
00:00:22,640 --> 00:00:25,489
Look for ideas to make things worth more.

8
00:00:25,679 --> 00:00:29,969
A thing, whether it be a vacant lot, a house, or a business,

9
00:00:30,160 --> 00:00:33,969
has value in proportion to the ideas for using it.

10
00:00:33,969 --> 00:00:35,570
2.

11
00:00:35,840 --> 00:00:38,530
Practice adding value to people.

12
00:00:38,640 --> 00:00:45,650
As you move higher and higher in the world of success, more and more of your job becomes people development.

13
00:00:46,080 --> 00:00:50,370
Ask, what can I do to add value to my subordinates?

14
00:00:50,480 --> 00:00:53,650
What can I do to help them to become more effective?

15
00:00:53,920 --> 00:00:59,489
Remember, to bring out the best in a person, you must first visualize his best.

16
00:00:59,489 --> 00:01:01,090
3.

17
00:01:01,280 --> 00:01:03,810
Practice adding value to yourself.

18
00:01:04,000 --> 00:01:06,530
Conduct a daily interview with yourself.

19
00:01:06,640 --> 00:01:11,010
Ask, what can I do to make myself more valuable today?

20
00:01:11,280 --> 00:01:15,010
Visualize yourself not as you are, but as you can be.

21
00:01:15,280 --> 00:01:20,050
Then specific ways for attaining your potential value will suggest themselves.

22
00:01:20,240 --> 00:01:21,969
Just try and see.

